Fit Saturated Model - Structural Equation Modeling

Source: R/fit.cov.R
fit.cov.Rd

Fits covariances and means of \(x\), \(m\), and \(y\) using structural equation modeling.

fit.cov(data)

Arguments

data

n by 3 matrix or data frame. data[, 1] correspond to values for x. data[, 2] correspond to values for m. data[, 3] correspond to values for y.

Examples

library(lavaan)
#> This is lavaan 0.6-7
#> lavaan is BETA software! Please report any bugs.
taskid <- 1

# Complete Data ----------------------------------------------------
original <- mvn_dat(taskid = taskid)
cov(original)
#>          x        m        y
#> x 233.7298 165.6777 150.2163
#> m 165.6777 233.8884 188.1404
#> y 150.2163 188.1404 229.7362
colMeans(original)
#>         x         m         y 
#> 100.30898  99.86515  99.46294 

# Missing completely at random -------------------------------------
data <- mvn_dat_mcar(data = original, taskid = taskid)
out <- fit.cov(data = data)
summary(out)
